WEBVTT

00:04.733 --> 00:05.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.733 --> 00:07.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.200 --> 00:09.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
an abrupt about-face.

00:09.833 --> 00:14.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
President Trump bans
transgender people from
serving in the military,
a surprise move drawing

00:16.033 --> 00:18.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
criticism from both
sides of the aisle.

00:18.333 --> 00:23.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then: Free from the reign of
ISIS, the Iraqi city of Mosul
grapples with a new battle,

00:24.900 --> 00:28.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as revenge killings push it
deeper into a cycle of violence.

00:28.766 --> 00:32.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOM PORTEOUS, Deputy Program
Director, Human Rights Watch:
If you are continuing to commit

00:32.933 --> 00:37.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
abuses with impunity, then you
are simply sowing the seeds for
the reemergence of extremism

00:41.166 --> 00:43.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and radicalism in Iraq.

00:43.200 --> 00:47.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And what
football does to the mind -- the
shocking results of a study that

00:49.333 --> 00:53.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
found brain damage in almost all
professional football players.

00:53.600 --> 00:56.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on
tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:56.066 --> 01:00.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:00.366 --> 01:05.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: From
President Trump today,
an abrupt announcement.

01:11.800 --> 01:16.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He is reinstating a ban
on transgender troops,
and reopening the debate
on who gets to serve

01:18.433 --> 01:20.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the U.S. military.

01:20.966 --> 01:25.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Word of the military policy
reversal came not from the
Pentagon, but from the president

01:27.133 --> 01:29.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on Twitter.

01:29.233 --> 01:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said: "The United States
government will not accept or
allow transgender individuals

01:34.400 --> 01:38.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to serve in any capacity
in the U.S. military."

01:38.133 --> 01:43.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he went on: "Our military
must be focused on victory,
and cannot be burdened with the

01:45.166 --> 01:49.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tremendous medical costs and
disruption that transgender
in the military would entail."

01:51.033 --> 01:54.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Candidate Trump had promised
to protect the rights
of transgender people.

01:54.800 --> 01:58.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
White House Press Secretary
Sarah Huckabee Sanders was
asked about that today.

01:58.766 --> 02:00.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH HUCKABEE SANDERS, INCOMING
WHITE HOUSE PRESS SECRETARY:
He's also voiced that this

02:00.833 --> 02:05.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is a very expensive and
disruptive policy, and based on
consultation that he's had with

02:05.433 --> 02:10.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his national security team, came
to the conclusion that it erodes
military readiness and unit

02:11.600 --> 02:14.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
cohesion, and made the
decision based on that.

02:14.600 --> 02:19.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Socially
conservative groups
welcomed the decision, but
it drew quick condemnation

02:21.366 --> 02:24.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from many Democrats,
including New York Congressman
Sean Patrick Maloney.

02:24.133 --> 02:26.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:26.200 --> 02:28.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEAN PATRICK MALONEY (D), New
York: We have heard every tired
-- every tired discriminatory

02:28.266 --> 02:33.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
argument before, and they have
always fallen away over time in
the face of reason and decency

02:34.600 --> 02:36.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and equality.

02:36.666 --> 02:40.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Some leading
members of the president's own
party also rejected the new

02:40.266 --> 02:45.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ban, including Senators John
McCain and Orrin Hatch and Joni
Ernst, who served in the U.S.

02:47.166 --> 02:49.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
military in Iraq.

02:49.700 --> 02:51.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ASHTON CARTER, Former
U.S. Secretary Of Defense:
I'm announcing today
that we're ending the

02:51.233 --> 02:54.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ban on transgender Americans
in the United States military.

02:54.133 --> 02:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All of this
comes more than a year after the
Obama administration's secretary

03:01.066 --> 03:04.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of defense, Ashton Carter,
announced that transgender
people would be allowed to serve

03:04.966 --> 03:07.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
openly.

03:07.100 --> 03:11.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The RAND Cooperation
estimates there are up
to 6,600 transgender
troops on active duty,

03:13.133 --> 03:16.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with possibly another
4,000 in the Reserves.

03:16.466 --> 03:20.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Carter gave the armed services
until this month to adjust.

03:20.366 --> 03:25.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But his successor, James Mattis,
recently delayed implementation
by another six months.

03:27.366 --> 03:31.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Joint Chiefs of Staff said
they need to determine whether
transgender recruits have

03:33.600 --> 03:36.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
medical issues affecting
their ability to deploy and
meet physical standards.

03:39.233 --> 03:43.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republican Congresswoman
Vicky Hartzler of Missouri
has unsuccessfully
proposed legislation

03:44.700 --> 03:46.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to bar medical services
for transgender troops.

03:46.833 --> 03:48.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:48.933 --> 03:50.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
VICKY HARTZLER (R), Missouri:
The bottom line is, do we need
to spend any of our precious

03:50.966 --> 03:55.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tax dollars on these surgeries,
when we have soldiers that are
having trouble getting body

03:56.700 --> 03:59.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
armor and bullets?

03:59.266 --> 04:02.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Brynn
Tannehill is a transgender
former Navy pilot, and
director for an advocacy

04:04.133 --> 04:06.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
group that fights for
transgender service members.

04:06.500 --> 04:07.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
LT.

04:07.500 --> 04:09.566 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
CMDR.

04:09.566 --> 04:11.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BRYNN TANNEHILL (RET.)
ÑMD-BOÑU.S. Navy:
What's extraordinarily
disruptive to unit

04:11.600 --> 04:14.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cohesion is taking people who
have unique, valuable skills
within their units, and yanking

04:16.166 --> 04:19.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
them out of those units,
ones that are often only
one deep in their units.

04:19.366 --> 04:20.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And you can't replace that.

04:20.833 --> 04:23.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what affects mission
and mission accomplishment.

04:23.533 --> 04:28.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The White
House indicated today
that the military will
take the lead on deciding

04:29.933 --> 04:33.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what becomes of transgender
people already serving.

04:33.033 --> 04:37.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our own William Brangham has
reported on transgender people
serving in the military.

04:37.633 --> 04:41.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He joins me now to
further explain today's
move by the president.

04:41.366 --> 04:43.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, William, first,
something about the term.

04:43.200 --> 04:45.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We are talking about
people who are transgender.

04:45.900 --> 04:49.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The term transition or
transitioning is also used.

04:49.900 --> 04:51.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Help us understand
the distinction.

04:51.733 --> 04:54.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: I understand
this can be confusing
for a lot of people.

04:54.033 --> 04:56.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Just basic facts.

04:56.133 --> 05:00.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
To be transgender just
means that your gender
identity doesn't match
your birth certificate.

05:01.666 --> 05:03.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, you're born as female, but
you do not feel you're female.

05:03.900 --> 05:05.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You feel like you're a male.

05:05.466 --> 05:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
To transition can mean a
whole spectrum of things.

05:08.933 --> 05:12.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It can mean -- it's not just
the surgery people tend to think
of, and certainly not every

05:12.933 --> 05:15.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
transgender person
has that surgery.

05:15.233 --> 05:16.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It can simply mean
taking hormones.

05:16.733 --> 05:20.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It can just mean changing your
clothes, changing your name.

05:20.600 --> 05:25.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, transitioning can be an
entire spectrum from things,
from medical technologies to

05:25.466 --> 05:27.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
just changing your
personality a little.

05:27.600 --> 05:30.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, we heard
the president - - the press
secretary at the White House,

05:30.466 --> 05:34.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sarah Sanders, citing the
president's concerns, and
he tweeted about this.

05:34.366 --> 05:38.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He says it's expensive,
the cost, the disruption.

05:38.433 --> 05:41.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She talked about
readiness, unit cohesion.

05:41.400 --> 05:44.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Are those factors that the
Pentagon is concerned about?

05:44.700 --> 05:48.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: As far as we
know, there's no good evidence
that the Pentagon has ever

05:48.833 --> 05:50.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
been concerned about
those two things.

05:50.866 --> 05:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the issue of disruption,
the RAND study that you cited
in your report, they did a

05:55.133 --> 06:00.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
study that looked at whether or
not having trans service members
would cause this disruption.

06:02.200 --> 06:05.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they surveyed 18 different
countries around the world,
including the U.K., Australia,

06:07.366 --> 06:10.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Israel, all of whom have
trans service members,
and those countries
reported no disruptions

06:11.900 --> 06:14.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
whatsoever, no need to
change their policies.

06:14.400 --> 06:19.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the issue of cost,
the president said
this is -- I think he's
implying that somehow this

06:19.066 --> 06:21.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is going to cost a
fortune for the budget.

06:21.200 --> 06:25.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Again, this RAND study
indicated that the rough costs
per year are about $2 million

06:25.833 --> 06:28.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to $8 million.

06:28.200 --> 06:31.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's not a lot in a $600
billion Pentagon budget.

06:31.233 --> 06:34.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And just for point of
comparison, let's say
those RAND numbers are
totally wrong and it's

06:34.266 --> 06:36.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
even more.

06:36.300 --> 06:40.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Pentagon right now spends
10 times that amount on Cialis
and Viagra, so just as a

06:42.400 --> 06:43.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
point of comparison.

06:43.633 --> 06:46.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Another
kind of medication.

06:46.366 --> 06:49.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
William, why is
this happening now?

06:49.033 --> 06:52.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is there a sense out of the
blue the president tweeted
about this, this morning?

06:52.766 --> 06:54.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: It did
seem to come out of the blue.

06:54.566 --> 06:57.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
In fact, we reached out
to the Pentagon today
to ask them about that.

06:57.300 --> 07:01.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And an indication of how much
they were caught flat-footed
about this, they had nothing to

07:01.733 --> 07:03.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
say and referred us
back to the White House.

07:03.733 --> 07:06.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
My sense is that
there's two reasons.

07:06.533 --> 07:11.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One, ever since the Obama
administration introduced
this change, there have
been social conservatives,

07:12.966 --> 07:15.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mike Pence in particular, who
have been very resistant to it.

07:15.533 --> 07:18.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They think it's social
engineering of the worst kind.

07:18.200 --> 07:19.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The
vice president.

07:19.200 --> 07:20.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Exactly.

07:20.200 --> 07:22.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And they have fought it.

07:22.233 --> 07:25.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, today, very specifically,
there was a fight in the
House amongst the GOP -- they

07:25.533 --> 07:29.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were trying to getting
a spending bill passed
with all sorts of goodies
that the president

07:29.333 --> 07:32.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
wanted, including money
for his border wall.

07:32.566 --> 07:37.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some deficit and defense
hawks said we need to put in a
piece of legislation that bans

07:38.666 --> 07:41.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
transgender sex
reassignment surgery.

07:41.500 --> 07:43.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That was pushed back
on by the leadership.

07:43.566 --> 07:46.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, apparently, some of these
members went to the president
and said, help us out with

07:46.600 --> 07:48.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this policy.

07:48.633 --> 07:52.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he then went 10, 50 yards
further down the line and
announced this outright ban.

07:54.966 --> 07:57.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, again,
we see divisions inside the
Republican Party over this.

07:57.433 --> 07:59.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Exactly.

07:59.566 --> 08:02.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, finally,
William, what does this mean
for active-duty members now

08:02.466 --> 08:05.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who are transgender,
whether they're serving in
this country or overseas?

08:05.433 --> 08:07.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That's
the great unknown.

08:07.500 --> 08:10.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sarah Huckabee Sanders said,
we're working out the policy.

08:10.066 --> 08:12.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Pentagon has
no comment on this.

08:12.866 --> 08:17.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I talked to some people today
who are in touch with trans
service members right now, and

08:17.466 --> 08:22.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they said that there is an
incredible feeling of fear and
panic and just uncertainty, that

08:23.200 --> 08:24.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
you have signed up.

08:24.433 --> 08:26.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You might be deployed
overseas right now.

08:26.533 --> 08:29.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All of a sudden, you look at
your phone, the president has
tweeted that your position in

08:29.666 --> 08:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the military is over, so
big unanswered questions.

08:33.400 --> 08:35.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A number
of questions here.

08:35.466 --> 08:38.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
William Brangham, we thank you.

08:38.500 --> 08:43.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in the day's other news: The
Supreme Court of South Carolina
ruled that same-sex couples

08:45.400 --> 08:48.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
deserve the same protections
from domestic violence
as heterosexual couples.

08:50.100 --> 08:52.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The court said that the
state's existing law
is unconstitutional.

08:52.533 --> 08:55.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Several other states
have already changed
their laws on the issue.

08:55.633 --> 09:00.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Activists expressed hope
that today's decision
encourages more to do so.

09:02.633 --> 09:05.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. Senate voted down a
proposal today to repeal the
Affordable Care Act two years

09:07.000 --> 09:09.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
from now, while it
works on a replacement.

09:09.333 --> 09:13.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was the latest sign that
it is going to be tougher to
win passage of a health care

09:13.166 --> 09:17.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
reform bill than it was
just simply to get the votes
yesterday to begin debate.

09:17.500 --> 09:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will have a full report on
this after the news summary.

09:22.033 --> 09:26.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump took a new
verbal shot at U.S. Attorney
General Jeff Sessions today.

09:26.300 --> 09:31.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Twitter, he complained that
Sessions ought to fire acting
FBI Director Andrew McCabe

09:33.300 --> 09:37.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for allegedly being too close
to his fired predecessor, James
Comey, and to Hillary Clinton.

09:39.733 --> 09:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Even so, White House Press
Secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders
left open the possibility

09:45.900 --> 09:48.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that the president may
decide to keep Sessions.

09:48.433 --> 09:52.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH HUCKABEE SANDERS:
He's obviously disappointed,
but also wants the attorney
general to continue

09:52.900 --> 09:56.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to focus on the things
