will continue to be.

20:02.400 --> 20:05.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I mean, what the Obama
administration, what
President Obama did was
take one issue, which

20:05.866 --> 20:10.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was a critical issue, not only
our national security experts,
but Israeli and other experts

20:10.400 --> 20:14.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
said, if Iran were to rush
to a bomb, we would be in
a very difficult situation.

20:14.933 --> 20:16.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Let's look at the
case of North Korea.

20:16.366 --> 20:19.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We wouldn't want to see a North
Korea in the Persian Gulf.

20:19.833 --> 20:24.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, that was a priority at
that point wasn't not to
give up on the other issues.

20:24.800 --> 20:28.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Let's at least make sure
that Iran is not in a
position to get a bomb.

20:28.400 --> 20:31.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At the same time, let's
push back on their
regional activities,
let's see what we can

20:31.333 --> 20:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do about their ballistic
missiles, but the deal itself --
and deliberately -- was about

20:35.900 --> 20:36.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this issue.

20:36.900 --> 20:38.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It wasn't a case of myopia.

20:38.766 --> 20:40.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was a case of, we're
going to deal with the issue.

20:40.833 --> 20:42.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We solved it, at least
for the time being.

20:42.933 --> 20:44.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And let's work on the other
issues at the same time.

20:44.900 --> 20:48.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is nothing in the nuclear
deal that would prevent us
from taking action against

20:48.400 --> 20:52.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Iran if it engaged in
terrorism, ballistic missiles,
human rights violations.

20:52.966 --> 20:56.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The question at the heart
of what the president
said is whether we are
going to continue to

20:56.266 --> 21:01.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
honor our part of the deal,
to make sure that Iran also
honors its part and doesn't rush

21:02.866 --> 21:05.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to a nuclear bomb, so
that we don't have what
we now in North Korea.

21:05.300 --> 21:08.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
North Korea, we have a country
that has a nuclear bomb,
and we have no visibility on

21:08.733 --> 21:10.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
what they're doing.

21:10.700 --> 21:13.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Iran, we have a country that
doesn't have a nuclear bomb,
and we have almost maximum

21:13.400 --> 21:17.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
visibility as a result of
the deal in every aspect
of their nuclear program.

21:17.133 --> 21:21.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mark Dubowitz,
what about that, the idea that
it's better to know what is

21:21.033 --> 21:25.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
going on, to work within
this agreement and know
what Iran is doing?

21:25.166 --> 21:30.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK DUBOWITZ: Well, I'm glad
Rob brought up the fatally
flawed North Korea nuclear

21:32.166 --> 21:34.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agreement, because the
Iran nuclear agreement is
similarly fatally flawed.

21:34.633 --> 21:39.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It contains within it
sunset provisions, where
the restrictions of
Iran's nuclear program

21:39.300 --> 21:44.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
actually go away over time, and
Iran can emerge, by actually
faithfully complying with the

21:44.033 --> 21:49.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
deal, with an industrial sized
nuclear program, with near zero
nuclear breakout capability,

21:51.533 --> 21:54.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with a much easier covert
sneak-out capability
with an ICBM, with a
powerful economy fortified

21:56.700 --> 21:59.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
against our ability to
use sanctions, and with
increased regional hegemony.

21:59.233 --> 22:01.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, Rob is right.

22:01.333 --> 22:06.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The deal temporarily pushed the
Iranians further in terms of
breakout, but over the medium

22:08.466 --> 22:11.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
term, Iran is going to emerge
with everything it wants by
faithfully complying with the

22:11.766 --> 22:13.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
deal.

22:13.766 --> 22:16.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we don't want another
fatally flawed nuclear agreement
like we had with North Korea.

22:16.400 --> 22:19.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What we need to start dealing
with is this flawed agreement.

22:19.566 --> 22:24.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think the president has
already made it very clear that
he thinks this is a terrible

22:24.366 --> 22:26.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
deal, he thinks it's
a fatally flawed deal.

22:26.566 --> 22:31.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think my advice to him
is don't certify compliance
and begin to lay the predicate

22:33.466 --> 22:36.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for a massive pressure campaign
and get the Iranians back
to the table to negotiate a

22:36.866 --> 22:41.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nuclear deal number two that
addresses some of these fatally
flawed elements of the deal,

22:43.733 --> 22:46.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and, by the way, give us
inspection rights into military
sites, which, right now, we

22:46.233 --> 22:50.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
have in theory, but, in
practice, the Iranians
aren't letting us into
their military sites,

22:50.233 --> 22:54.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
where they're likely to engage
in nuclear weaponization
activities like they have in

22:54.000 --> 22:56.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the past.

22:56.066 --> 22:58.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we better rectify this
fatally flawed deal, or the
Iranians are going to a nuke,

22:58.866 --> 23:03.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ICBMs, and they're going to have
the ability to dominate like
nothing we have seen before.

23:03.833 --> 23:05.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Rob Malley, what
would be the consequences?

23:05.633 --> 23:07.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What is at stake here?

23:07.766 --> 23:11.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What would be the consequences
if the president did say Iran
is not living up to this deal?

23:11.700 --> 23:14.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROB MALLEY: Well, first, I
have to say, I'm a little bit
confused about argument that

23:14.566 --> 23:16.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Mark was making.

23:16.566 --> 23:19.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is the argument that the deal is
fatally flawed and, therefore,
we shouldn't accept it, we

23:19.133 --> 23:22.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
should walk away, we
should renegotiate it,
which would be one path?

23:22.000 --> 23:23.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Very dangerous.

23:23.000 --> 23:25.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I won't get into that.

23:25.066 --> 23:29.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Or is his view, the deal is
OK for now, but in 12, 13, 14,
15 years, as some provisions

23:31.100 --> 23:34.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
are going to expire, and
so we should think of
whether we can negotiate
what happens afterwards,

23:34.466 --> 23:36.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
but in which case we're
going to give something
to Iranians in return.

23:36.600 --> 23:39.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nobody is going to -- the
Iranians are not going to accept
to negotiate more restrictions

23:39.600 --> 23:40.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in exchange for nothing.

23:40.600 --> 23:42.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, I think we need to clarify.

23:42.600 --> 23:46.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Right now, we're in a much
better position than we were at
the time President Obama took

23:46.766 --> 23:49.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
office, because we have
these restrictions.

23:49.000 --> 23:54.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And according to every
inspection that has been done,
every report by the IAEA, Iran

23:54.833 --> 23:56.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is in compliance.

23:56.900 --> 23:59.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, if tomorrow, the president
were to decide to announce
that Iran is not in compliance,

23:59.066 --> 24:03.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
first of all, I think we
would have a little bit of
deja vu in terms of Iraq.

24:03.066 --> 24:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think most people in the
international community
would believe that
we're just fabricating

24:07.200 --> 24:10.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
evidence, because we
haven't shared it, because,
right now, we're the only
ones who are claiming

24:10.900 --> 24:13.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that Iran is not in --
or we would be the only
ones claiming that.

24:13.900 --> 24:15.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That would not put us
in a strong position.

24:15.933 --> 24:19.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If we were to do that, and
that is it, and continue to
honor the deal, it would be a

24:19.933 --> 24:21.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
hiccup.

24:21.966 --> 24:24.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It would once again signal
to the world that we have a
rather erratic administration.

24:24.633 --> 24:28.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If he were then to impose
sanctions, to reimpose
the sanctions that were
lifted, reimpose sanctions

24:28.900 --> 24:31.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on Iran's nuclear program,
then we would be in breach.

24:31.900 --> 24:36.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And either Iran would itself
say we're not only bound by
our own commitments, and we

24:38.800 --> 24:43.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have a possibility of Iran
trying to acquire a nuclear
bomb, or we would be isolated in

24:43.366 --> 24:46.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the international
community, because the
Europeans, the Russians,
the Chinese, everyone would

24:46.333 --> 24:47.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
say, it's on you.

24:47.733 --> 24:48.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's not on Iran.

24:48.733 --> 24:50.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Why would we want that?

24:50.233 --> 24:52.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mark Dubowitz, let
me -- I want you to respond.

24:52.633 --> 24:54.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What would happen?

24:54.600 --> 24:58.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What practically would
happen if the president
said they weren't complying?

24:59.800 --> 25:01.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And then what should
the next step be?

25:01.933 --> 25:04.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK DUBOWITZ: Well, actually,
practically speaking, what
Rob's not telling you is that,

25:04.833 --> 25:08.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
if the president says they're
not complying, but he doesn't
say that they're in material

25:08.500 --> 25:11.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
breach, then actually
nothing happens.

25:11.233 --> 25:12.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Then we don't go to
the joint commission.

25:12.966 --> 25:15.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We don't snap back U.N.
and U.S. sanctions.

25:15.400 --> 25:18.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We merely say Iran is engaging
in incremental violations.

25:18.766 --> 25:23.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we know that the Iranians
violate incrementally,
not egregiously, even
though, over time, the

25:23.266 --> 25:26.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
sum total of the incremental
violations is always egregious.

25:26.700 --> 25:31.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What Rob's not telling
you is that he knows and
we know that the Iranians
have been incrementally

25:31.066 --> 25:32.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
violating this deal.

25:32.333 --> 25:34.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They have exceeded
heavy water caps.

25:34.300 --> 25:38.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Heavy water is the
essential ingredient you
need for a plutonium bomb.

25:38.533 --> 25:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're testing more advanced
centrifuges than they are
permitted under the nuclear

25:41.833 --> 25:43.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
agreement.

25:43.800 --> 25:46.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have been illicitly
procuring nuclear and ballistic
missile technology in Germany,

25:46.700 --> 25:49.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
according to German
intelligence services.

25:49.333 --> 25:51.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And they have exceeded
their enrichment cap.

25:51.100 --> 25:53.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, the fact of the matter
is, there are violations.

25:53.233 --> 25:54.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're not material breaches.

25:54.766 --> 25:56.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're incremental violations.

25:56.733 --> 26:00.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president should state
that, certify that, and say
Iran is not in full compliance.

26:00.433 --> 26:03.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now, the second step is to say
whether it's a material breach.

26:03.800 --> 26:04.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And it's.

26:04.800 --> 26:06.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's not a material breach.

26:06.333 --> 26:07.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he should move ahead with
the maximum pressure campaign.

26:07.800 --> 26:08.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Mark
Dubowitz, I'm sorry.

26:08.966 --> 26:10.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We're out of time.

26:10.500 --> 26:11.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mark Dubowitz, Rob Malley, we're
going to have to leave it there.

26:11.766 --> 26:12.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you, gentlemen.

26:12.766 --> 26:14.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROB MALLEY: Thank you.

