29:39.366 --> 29:41.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
was taken last spring.

29:41.333 --> 29:45.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The hospital was inundated
with unidentified bodies
coming down the Tigris River.

29:45.900 --> 29:48.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The morgue could barely
handle the grim deluge.

29:48.633 --> 29:51.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A local resident described the
what he saw at the riverbank.

29:51.833 --> 29:55.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator):
They had their hands
tied behind their backs.

29:55.200 --> 29:57.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They were blindfolded
and shot in the head.

29:57.366 --> 29:58.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They were floating
down the river.

29:58.866 --> 30:02.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: And just last
week, even more bodies.

30:02.800 --> 30:06.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You received a lot of bodies
that looked to have been the
victims of execution, is that

30:06.866 --> 30:07.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
right?

30:07.866 --> 30:09.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Yes.

30:09.400 --> 30:10.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: What was the state
of the bodies that you received?

30:10.466 --> 30:12.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

30:12.500 --> 30:14.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MANSOUR MAAROUF MANSOUR, Iraq:
Yes, most of them were killed
by shooting to the head.

30:14.633 --> 30:19.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's very little in compared
to those who were killed by
the liberation process, through

30:21.233 --> 30:25.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the mines, land mines,
or the bombs, mortar
bombs, or airstrike.

30:27.000 --> 30:31.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: The number
of civilian casualties
has been staggering.

30:33.133 --> 30:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Former Kurdish Deputy Prime
Minister Hoshyar Zebari says
at least 40,000 dead, many of

30:38.333 --> 30:42.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
them at the hands of coalition
airstrikes, which include both
Iraqi and American firepower.

30:44.533 --> 30:49.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
As residents return
home to a Mosul depleted
of ISIS fighters, the
new campaign may be

30:49.433 --> 30:54.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
one of collective
punishment against possible
ISIS sympathizers.

30:56.533 --> 30:59.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We traveled to a village just
south of the city, where many
of the residents collaborated

30:59.833 --> 31:01.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with ISIS.

31:01.933 --> 31:06.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We had heard reports of
so-called revenge death squads
coming for them in the dead of

31:06.833 --> 31:08.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
night.

31:08.900 --> 31:13.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Um Nazim's husband was a taxi
driver, and she says he just
joined the group to survive.

31:15.066 --> 31:17.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He was later killed
in an airstrike.

31:17.266 --> 31:20.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She was too scared to let
us show her full face.

31:20.100 --> 31:23.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UM NAZIM, Iraq (through
translator): They told us, if
your sons and husbands do not

31:23.833 --> 31:28.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
declare loyalty, we will bring
back the religious police
and we will behead them.

31:28.000 --> 31:30.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He was an old man when we were
threatened, so he was scared.

31:30.666 --> 31:33.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He thought it would be
better to declare loyalty.

31:33.100 --> 31:35.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It is better than being killed.

31:35.333 --> 31:40.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: Since the
liberation of her town
from ISIS, she says
local militias have

31:42.266 --> 31:45.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
threatened her, demanding
that she leave, even shooting
up and raiding her home.

31:45.033 --> 31:49.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
UM NAZIM (through translator):
We have lost our minds.

31:49.033 --> 31:52.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Every night when we sleep,
we don't know if we will
be alive in the morning.

31:52.333 --> 31:54.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What is our life?

31:54.433 --> 31:57.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We were all throwing their
clothes in bags, but we
didn't know where to go.

31:57.533 --> 32:00.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We don't have money to
leave or even to rent a car.

32:00.733 --> 32:03.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I don't know what
to do, where to go.

32:03.466 --> 32:05.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I was pacing back and
forth in the front yard.

32:05.600 --> 32:07.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I told them, kill me.

32:07.700 --> 32:09.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's better than this.

32:09.200 --> 32:11.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Come on and kill me
and end my suffering.

32:11.166 --> 32:16.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: The Iraqi
government maintains that any
abuse is being dealt with in due

32:17.433 --> 32:19.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
process, and Iraqi commanders
admit the mistakes.

32:19.533 --> 32:20.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
MAJ.

32:20.533 --> 32:21.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

32:21.933 --> 32:22.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NAJIM AL-JUBOURI, Iraqi
Commander: We don't lead eagles.

32:22.600 --> 32:24.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We lead humans.

32:24.233 --> 32:29.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I mean, our soldiers,
our police, they are
human, not eagles.

32:31.100 --> 32:36.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Maybe someone make some bad
thing, but the majority, the
general of our forces deal very

32:40.666 --> 32:42.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
good with the people.

32:42.733 --> 32:46.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: So what do you
do when you find out one of
your men has been part of this

32:47.300 --> 32:48.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
abuse?

32:48.300 --> 32:49.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
MAJ.

32:49.300 --> 32:51.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

32:51.033 --> 32:54.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
NAJIM AL-JUBOURI: We put
him in the jail, and we
send him to the court.

32:54.800 --> 32:56.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
e

32:56.900 --> 33:00.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Do you worry about
revenge attacks creating an
atmosphere that would make Iraq

33:01.666 --> 33:02.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
vulnerable to another ISIS?

33:02.766 --> 33:03.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
MAJ.

33:03.766 --> 33:05.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

33:05.000 --> 33:08.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
NAJIM AL-JUBOURI: Yes,
I worry about that.

33:08.500 --> 33:13.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We try to push the local
government to put some
solution to these things.

33:20.000 --> 33:22.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Human rights
groups say this is not enough.

33:22.766 --> 33:25.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOM PORTEOUS, Deputy Program
Director, Human Rights Watch:
The Iraqi government sometimes

33:25.933 --> 33:30.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
responds to our reports and
our advocacy by making the
right sort of noises and making

33:34.733 --> 33:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the right kinds of statements,
but it's never followed up with
a proper procedure to secure

33:41.033 --> 33:43.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
accountability for the
abuses that we document.

33:43.833 --> 33:48.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You can win the war militarily
against the Islamic State,
but if you are continuing to

33:51.766 --> 33:56.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
commit abuses with impunity,
then you are simply sowing
the seeds for the reemergence

33:58.900 --> 34:01.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of extremism and
radicalism in Iraq.

34:01.833 --> 34:06.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Like many Sunni
Arabs that lived under ISIS, Um
Nazim feels she is under siege

34:08.766 --> 34:12.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by the Shia-dominated government
and militias that fought and
won the battle against ISIS.

34:13.400 --> 34:15.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Do you hope that
ISIS will come back?

34:15.866 --> 34:20.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UM NAZIM (through translator):
I don't hope that ISIS will
come back, but there was peace

34:20.400 --> 34:23.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and no one interfered in
the life of anyone else.

34:23.000 --> 34:24.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
No one oppressed anyone.

34:24.166 --> 34:26.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The situation was calmer.

34:26.200 --> 34:29.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: For you, but
for those who weren't part of
ISIS, they were very scared.

34:29.300 --> 34:32.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
UM NAZIM (through translator):
No, no one in Iraq was scared.

34:32.833 --> 34:37.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Everybody was living in peace
under ISIS, not just us, because
my husband was with ISIS.

34:37.666 --> 34:40.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: But
how can you say that?

34:40.300 --> 34:45.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have heard so many stories
of people who were killed,
people who were repressed, who

34:46.600 --> 34:48.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
couldn't go to school?

34:48.000 --> 34:49.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
UM NAZIM (through
translator): I don't know.

34:49.333 --> 34:51.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I didn't go out.

34:51.033 --> 34:52.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I didn't see anything.

34:52.400 --> 34:55.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I'm only responsible for
myself, not for others.

34:55.433 --> 34:58.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I didn't see anyone kill
anyone else in front of me.

34:58.533 --> 35:02.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I heard people say that
others were killed, but
who knows who killed them.

35:02.666 --> 35:07.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: What do you say
to the children whose parents
were killed by ISIS suicide

35:09.200 --> 35:10.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
bombers?

35:10.600 --> 35:11.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
UM NAZIM (through
translator): I don't know.

35:11.500 --> 35:12.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I didn't see.

35:12.966 --> 35:15.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I wasn't with ISIS to
know anything about that.

35:15.766 --> 35:18.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ISIS became a state
and a government.

35:18.500 --> 35:20.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Who can say anything to
them under their rule?

35:20.900 --> 35:25.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Like many under
occupation, Um Nazim turned a
blind eye in order to ensure

35:27.466 --> 35:30.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
her own safety.

35:30.100 --> 35:35.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The dust is beginning
to settle in Mosul, but
revenge can be a dirty game.

35:37.033 --> 35:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The battle may have ended,
but a new war in Iraq
may be just beginning.

35:42.000 --> 35:45.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Marcia Biggs in
and around Mosul, Iraq.

35:48.466 --> 35:53.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Earlier this
month, Walter Shaub resigned
as director of the federal

35:59.333 --> 36:04.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Office of Government
Ethics, a position he's
held since January 2013.

36:06.266 --> 36:09.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the final months of his
tenure, Shaub clashed with the
Trump administration on a number

36:09.666 --> 36:11.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of ethics issues.

36:11.566 --> 36:15.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Currently, he is senior
director of ethics for the
nonprofit Campaign Legal Center.

36:16.533 --> 36:17.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And Mr. Shaub joins me now.

36:17.933 --> 36:20.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Thank you for being
here at the "NewsHour."

36:20.066 --> 36:22.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, you had been -- you were
just telling me you had been
at the Office of Government

36:22.900 --> 36:25.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Ethics for, what, 15, 16 years?

36:25.000 --> 36:26.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WALTER SHAUB, Campaign
Legal Center: Right.

36:26.933 --> 36:29.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Leading up
to your decision to resign.

36:29.333 --> 36:32.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You had another six months to
go as director of the office.

36:32.866 --> 36:34.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Why leave?

36:34.066 --> 36:35.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Why not stay until
the end, next January?

36:35.566 --> 36:37.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WALTER SHAUB: Well, first of
all, thanks for having me.

36:37.800 --> 36:42.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I started at OGE in 2001 and
have served there continuously,
except for two years, when I

36:44.866 --> 36:47.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
left.

36:47.300 --> 36:50.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have seen OGE operate
under three different
presidential administrations
right now, including

36:52.800 --> 36:56.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the administrations of President
Bush and President Obama, who
were incredibly supportive

36:56.533 --> 36:59.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of the ethics program.

36:59.166 --> 37:04.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Both of those administrations
really supported OGE
in absolutely every
way they could, and

37:05.266 --> 37:07.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
our work functioned
very smoothly.

37:07.933 --> 37:12.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
In the past eight
months, we have departed
from ethical norms.

37:15.366 --> 37:18.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the program is under
significant pressure
from the White House
that has set a tone there

37:19.133 --> 37:21.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the top that ethics
doesn't matter.

37:21.266 --> 37:25.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I did all I could,
and I reached a point where
I thought there wasn't more I

37:25.666 --> 37:27.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
could achieve from inside.

37:27.633 --> 37:32.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, by leaving, I would
actually have more freedom to
continue to try to push for the

37:33.466 --> 37:34.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
restoration of our
ethics program.

37:34.966 --> 37:37.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you have
been speaking out since then.

37:37.100 --> 37:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Give us an example of the way or
ways that this administration,
as you say, was putting

37:41.833 --> 37:44.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
stress on the ethics procedures.

37:44.566 --> 37:49.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WALTER SHAUB: Well, in one
way, it really began with the
president declaring that he's

37:50.700 --> 37:53.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
not going to divest his
financial interests.

37:53.333 --> 37:57.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that means there is a
cloud over all government
decision-making that
stems from the president,

37:59.933 --> 38:03.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because you can't know whether
his decisions are being made
on the basis of policy aims

38:04.866 --> 38:06.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
or on the basis of
financial interests.

38:06.900 --> 38:11.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when he travels to all of
his properties on a frequent
basis, he's giving each of them

38:11.533 --> 38:15.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
free advertisements, and he
speaks freely about those.

38:15.166 --> 38:19.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He could have, instead,
divested his interests and
told his administration
to stay away there

38:19.966 --> 38:24.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his properties, which would
have kept some of the foreign
governments or charities or

38:26.966 --> 38:30.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
businesses that have booked his
business -- his properties to
be closer to the president not

38:31.766 --> 38:33.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to do that.

38:33.300 --> 38:38.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think a lot of things happen
on a day-to-day basis as well.

38:38.033 --> 38:43.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I fought a battle that took
over a month to get them to
release some waivers that they

38:44.433 --> 38:46.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
had been issuing, and OGE's
collection of waivers...

38:46.533 --> 38:47.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: To individuals.

38:47.700 --> 38:49.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WALTER SHAUB: To
individual appointees.

38:49.666 --> 38:53.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And OGE's collection of waivers
and other ethics documents
has been a routine function

38:53.866 --> 38:57.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of OGE's program dating all
the way back to its beginning.

38:57.233 --> 39:01.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OGE is by statute the
supervising Ethics Office.

39:01.300 --> 39:06.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I finally got the waivers,
I was shocked to see that a
number of them, most of them,

39:08.766 --> 39:11.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
actually, were unsigned,
undated, either explicitly
or implicitly retroactive,
and two of them

39:13.666 --> 39:16.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
were issued by the counselor
of the president to a group of
people that included himself.

39:16.833 --> 39:19.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, that's about as bad an
ethics program as you can run.

39:19.966 --> 39:23.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, now you
know that -- what the White
House has been saying since you

39:23.200 --> 39:24.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
left your position.

39:24.300 --> 39:25.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They were criticizing
you before.

39:25.666 --> 39:27.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They have been
criticizing since.

