adds in the ongoing quest for

43:22.800 --> 43:25.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a better understanding of CTE.

43:25.500 --> 43:30.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The NFL will continue to work
with a wide range of experts
to improve the health of

43:30.133 --> 43:33.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
current and former
NFL athletes."

43:33.333 --> 43:37.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Michael Alosco is a co-author
of the study from the Boston
University CTE Center.

43:37.766 --> 43:39.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Michael, thanks for joining us.

43:39.900 --> 43:43.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
