there might be something wrong.

43:50.600 --> 43:53.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That said, what does this
information tell you?

43:53.233 --> 43:55.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What does this data point to?

43:55.300 --> 43:57.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MICHAEL ALOSCO, Boston
University CTE Center:
This is the largest case
series study to date

43:57.833 --> 43:59.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of CTE.

43:59.100 --> 44:02.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You know, it's among
football players.

44:02.666 --> 44:07.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The sheer numbers, the sheer
size of the individuals who
had CTE is really concerning.

44:09.533 --> 44:14.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's really suggesting a link
between prior participation
in football and CTE.

44:16.200 --> 44:20.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's really going to serve as
a foundation, as a rich data
source going forward to really

44:22.400 --> 44:26.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
