right-hand side, you see
a lot more dark edges.

45:20.666 --> 45:22.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And that, I suppose,
is where the CTE is.

45:22.466 --> 45:24.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But what -- how does this
affect a player's behavior?

45:24.933 --> 45:29.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MICHAEL ALOSCO: We see
a lot of different types
of symptoms in CTE.

45:29.133 --> 45:33.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A lot of them are nonspecific,
meaning that, you know, we see
these symptoms across various

45:33.866 --> 45:36.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
conditions.

45:36.000 --> 45:39.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
However, in CTE, we're
commonly seeing behavior
changes, so we're seeing
aggressive behaviors,

45:40.866 --> 45:42.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
violent behaviors.

45:42.100 --> 45:44.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We're seeing changes in
mood, like depression.

45:44.266 --> 45:49.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we're also seeing changes
in thinking and memory.

45:49.100 --> 45:53.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What we need to identify is what
symptoms are specific to CTE.

45:53.600 --> 45:58.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And by doing that, it will
help us diagnose CTE in life
and really characterize it.

45:58.566 --> 46:02.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: One of the
things I found interesting was
that you actually found this

46:02.400 --> 46:04.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
