49:38.233 --> 49:39.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to you?

49:39.233 --> 49:41.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: Yes.

49:41.133 --> 49:45.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, I found all of them online
through pro-Trump Facebook
groups, Women for Trump.

49:45.166 --> 49:46.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It was really hard
to gain their trust.

49:46.833 --> 49:49.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A lot of them had no
interested in speaking to me.

49:49.100 --> 49:54.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is a perception that the
media is very liberal, very
biased, produces fake news.

49:56.100 --> 49:58.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Some of them said they'd
speak to me and later
made the decision that
they didn't want to.

49:58.433 --> 50:03.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And one of the women I met in
a public park because she said:
"I'm concerned about meeting

50:03.900 --> 50:05.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you.

50:05.366 --> 50:06.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know what you're
going to do when I meet you.

50:06.300 --> 50:07.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Maybe you will try to hurt me.

50:07.833 --> 50:09.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I think we should met
in a public place."

50:09.600 --> 50:13.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So there was a lot of
fear of the media and
how they're portrayed.

50:13.000 --> 50:16.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tell us about
what it's like for them?

50:16.933 --> 50:20.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do they go through as they
express their political views?

50:20.733 --> 50:24.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: Well,
they certainly get a lot of
pushback for their beliefs.

50:24.600 --> 50:28.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And some of them do have more
extreme beliefs, to be certain.

50:28.866 --> 50:33.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Others hold more moderate
views, but they're all sort of
clumped together as one thing.

50:33.633 --> 50:37.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They're called racists
and bigots regularly.

50:37.933 --> 50:39.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And they're attacked online.

50:39.566 --> 50:41.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They're told that
they should go die.

50:41.933 --> 50:46.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One woman told me, one day,
when she was walking her dog and
wearing a Trump hat, a man just

50:46.200 --> 50:49.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
stopped to say to her: "Your
kind isn't wanted here.

50:49.433 --> 50:51.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You should just leave."

50:51.933 --> 50:56.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if they go to these
rallies, they face even
more of an extreme reaction.

50:58.966 --> 51:01.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Many people in Portland, in the
Pacific Northwest come out to
counterprotest these rallies.

51:01.900 --> 51:06.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And some of them are
more liberal Portlanders
who just want to say,
I don't agree with what

51:06.200 --> 51:08.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you have to say.

51:08.200 --> 51:12.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But others are militant leftists
that show up and basically
say, we're unapologetic about

51:13.533 --> 51:16.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
using physical violence
against these Trump supporters.

51:16.233 --> 51:21.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, certainly, violence happens
on both sides, but the militant
leftists are very unapologetic

51:21.966 --> 51:23.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and open about it.

51:23.966 --> 51:25.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I think, for
people who didn't realize
it, it's eye-opening.

51:25.433 --> 51:27.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One of the women you talked
to, Liz, is transgender.

51:27.833 --> 51:28.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: Yes.

51:28.833 --> 51:31.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Her name is Athena Brown.

51:31.300 --> 51:35.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Athena switched parties
from being a Democrat
to being a Republican
in mid-2016, just before

51:37.533 --> 51:39.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the election.

51:39.600 --> 51:43.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She became fed up, she said,
with what she saw as political
correctness on the left and

51:44.700 --> 51:47.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in the liberal LGBT community.

51:47.533 --> 51:51.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she told me: "You know,
when I became - - when I came
out as transgender, I lost

51:51.666 --> 51:53.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
two friends.

51:53.200 --> 51:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
When I came out as Republican,
I lost 100 friends on Facebook."

51:56.300 --> 52:01.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so she really saw that
as an example of the left's
intolerance to people who do not

52:02.033 --> 52:03.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
share their views.

52:03.266 --> 52:05.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How do
these women keep going?

52:05.333 --> 52:09.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In that environment, where
they are such a minority,
what keeps them going?

52:10.333 --> 52:12.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How do they deal with it?

52:12.366 --> 52:16.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: I think they're
actually invigorated by the
pushback that they're getting.

52:18.500 --> 52:21.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think they really feel that
it's worth, it's important to
go out and defend what they

52:23.033 --> 52:25.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
see as an attack on free speech.

52:25.633 --> 52:30.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, you know, one of the
interesting things I saw is, as
the left tried to shut down what

52:32.566 --> 52:36.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they had to say, these Trump
supporters, these women were
more determined to go out and to

52:37.333 --> 52:39.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
speak.

52:39.433 --> 52:41.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They just wanted to get more
active and became more even
strident in their beliefs.

52:41.800 --> 52:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, in a way,
it was a mirror image of the
anti-Trump women you talked to

52:47.666 --> 52:48.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in conservative West Virginia.

52:48.866 --> 52:50.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: Absolutely.

52:50.966 --> 52:54.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In both places, I think, as
people tried to shut down what
they had to say, these women

52:54.633 --> 52:56.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
just wanted to speak out louder.

52:56.400 --> 52:58.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They wanted to get more
involved and more active.

52:58.966 --> 53:03.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, in both places, it felt
like people on opposite sides
of the political divide were

53:05.100 --> 53:07.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
not speaking to each other.

53:07.066 --> 53:11.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They were speaking past each
other, and there was no interest
in really hearing what the

53:11.233 --> 53:12.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
other side had to say.

53:12.933 --> 53:15.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Discouraging,
but some great reporting.

